    <stitle>INSTRUMENTS (Data Link Driven Instrument Cluster) - FE 300 and IC Bus - DESCRIPTION - SPEEDOMETER GAUGE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SPEEDOMETER GAUGE</title>
        <para>An electronic speedometer gauge (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0831302">Figure 2</hotlnk>) is located in the instrument cluster and it indicates miles and
            kilometers per hour. The electronic speedometer system consists of the dash mounted air core gauge,
            microprocessor, transmission mounted vehicle speed sensor (VSS), engine ECM2, data link and circuits that
            connect the units.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0831302" figsize="col-wide">
